# Methods in Java 🚀

## 🧠 What is a Method?
A **method** in Java is a block of code that performs a specific task.  
It allows **code reusability**, improves readability, and makes programs more organized.

### 📝 Syntax:

	returnType methodName(parameters) {
    // method body
	}

Types of Methods

	******Predefined Methods

	Already defined in Java libraries.

	Example: System.out.println().

	******User-defined Methods

	Defined by the user to perform specific tasks.

		⚡ Static 						vs 		Non-Static Methods
		Static Methods							Non-Static Methods
		Declared with the static keyword		No static keyword
		Can be called without creating object	Require object to call
		Example: main() method					Example: obj.display()